2. In these Regulations-                                                       interpretation.
       "recorded information" means any report, update, or notice
             transmitted to the Registry pursuant to regulation 3 or 6;
        .'Register" means the Children's Register established under section 5
             of the Act;
       "Registrar" means the Registrar appointed under regulation 14;
       "Registration Officer" means a person so appointed pursuant to
            regulation 15(3);
       "report" means a report made pursuant to section 6 of the Act;
       "the relevant child", in relation to any report, means the child in
            respect of whom the report is made;
       "the reporter", in relation to any report, means the person who makes,
             or is required to make (as the case may be), the report.
